# Deployment

- **Platform:** [Coolify](https://control.bamsignal.com) — self-hosted on the BamSignal server.
- **Production URL:** https://bamsignal.com
- **Do not use Vercel** for this repo (`.vercel/` is legacy/unused).

## How to deploy

1. Commit and push to `main` on `github.com/bamsignalhq/bamsignal`.
2. Before pushing, run the server import smoke test: `npm run test:server-import` (also enforced by the `.githooks/pre-push` hook after `npm install`).
3. Coolify rebuilds from the repo `Dockerfile` (`npm run build` → server import smoke test → `node server/production.js`).
4. Confirm deploy status in Coolify at control.bamsignal.com (manual redeploy if webhook did not fire).

## Build args / env (Coolify)

**Buildtime ON — public `VITE_*` only** (see `Dockerfile` builder stage):

- `VITE_SUPABASE_URL`, `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
- `VITE_FIREBASE_*` (api key, auth domain, project id, storage bucket, messaging sender id, app id)
- Other public client vars: `VITE_PUBLIC_APP_URL`, `VITE_PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY`, etc.

**Buildtime OFF — runtime secrets only** (injected when the container starts; never Docker `ARG`):

- `DATABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
- `PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY`, `RESEND_API_KEY`
- `SENDCHAMP_API_KEY`, `SENDCHAMP_WHATSAPP_SENDER`, `SENDCHAMP_SENDER`
- `FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON`, `FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY` (and discrete Firebase admin vars)
- `CRON_SECRET`, `ADMIN_ACTION_PIN`, `COMMAND_CENTER_PIN`

`/health` reports which runtime services are configured after deploy. The Docker build and smoke import must succeed **without** runtime secrets present.

See `.env.example` for the full list.
